The exact target output range is therefore `Sheet1!B1:B269`. Since the instruction asks to “apply the results to column B,” I should populate column B, not overwrite column A.

A robust formula for this conversion is `=A1&""`, filled down. It converts both numeric and string values into text in Excel/LibreOffice. I’ll also set column B cells to text format (`@`) to match intent. Then I’ll save to the output directory, recalculate, reload, verify sheet names, and print target cells/formulas/values from the first and last rows to confirm the results are present and non-blank.
